paragraph_text: We believe fun is infectious. It’s important. It’s not just for kids. That’s why Funlab is a leader in hospitality-driven entertainment. We’re dedicated to the creation, development, operation and management of directional entertainment concepts

We’re a privately held company whose family currently includes Strike Bowling Bar, Sky Zone Australia and Holey Moley Golf Club Australia and New Zealand, plus our newest brands to join the family, Archie Brothers Cirque Electriq and B. Lucky & Sons.

At the heart of Funlab is its people. They are a team of 1,300 and the ones that bring these concepts to life. From going above and beyond to keeping a positive and healthy mindset, the Funlab team practise these core values day in and day out.
We’re proud to have incredibly dedicated and passionate people across all roles and locations. We asked them why Funlab?
It’s seeing the change over all these years – especially the progression of our people nationwide.
It is a great place to work – so much opportunity if you want it and a great working environment, surrounded by great people.
Between my ambition, a company with a culture for driving and developing people and some great mentors, my personal drive has been a great match.
Honestly, I feel valued. I know my investment, passion and hunger is valued. It doesn’t feel like work when you love what you do.
It is without a doubt somewhere you create the fun and uniqueness is encouraged! It is an amazing company with so much room for growth and development.

Strike and Funlab have always been extremely invested in me and everything I have wanted to do. Strike has taught me so much both in my personal and professional life and I continue to learn each day.
Want to make your mark as a motherfunner? Check out our current opportunities.
Funlab wouldn't be what it is today if it weren't for the people. It's our 1,200+ Motherfunners that make us who we are.

A Motherfunner isn't a type of person, it's a certain quality. It's that positive mindset, and a strong will to enjoy yourself & to ensure others are enjoying themselves too. It's that kind of energy that beams out of someone when they're doing or talking about something they love.
You get a sense of FOMO when you're with our MOFOs (Motherfunners, thank you); you want what they're having. It's these type of people that make Funlab, Funlab.
Want to become a Motherfunner? Check out our positions that are available at the moment.

At the core of Funlab are our values. They determine how we make business decisions and how we treat each other and our guests. They aren’t just words on a poster in the staff room – they’re the heart of how we do things. If you understand our Core Values, you’ll understand what it means to be part of the Funlab team:
Positive Mind Set
Development + Investment + Nurturing = Growth
Fun is infectious, spread it.
Encouraging Our Uniqueness
Above & Beyond
Clear, Consistent and Collaborative Communication.
Recognise and Reward
Keep it Real, Honest & Unscripted
Always be Safe

One of our core values is developing and investing in our people – allowing them to grow. We call it DING (Development + Investment + Nurturing = Growth) and we’re serious about it. As we grow, you grow too.
In the spirit of continuous improvement, we’re always innovating – our brands and business evolve constantly. There’s always something new and exciting going on around here.

Putt, bowl, jump, soar, sing, escape, climb, pew-pew and play your heart out. Our Melbourne-based Support Office comes equipped with a multi-storey slippery dip, gym, trampolines and a couple of office puppies. It's pretty great.
